            <title>[HBASE-16482] Collect logs and other files when system tests fail</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-16482</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As requested by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=apurtell&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;apurtell&quot;&gt;Andrew Purtell&lt;/a&gt;, when &lt;tt&gt;hbase-it&lt;/tt&gt; jobs fail:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;To completely retrace a rare botch we may need persisted post run:
- The console log of the rum
- All daemon logs
- All WALs
- All HFiles
WALs and HFiles should be be organized by time from oldest to newest.

All could reside in a S3 bucket.
&lt;/pre&gt;
